title: 2012102512_wsp64knt120hr_halfDeg
name: 2012102512_wsp64knt120hr_halfDeg
description:
The 64 knot, 120 hour cumulative wind speed probabilities show 
probabilites of sustained (1-minute average) surface (10-meter altitude) 
wind speeds equal to or exceeding 64 kt...74 mph
(hurricane force) at a regualary spaced (1/2 degree) grid of points.  The 
cumulative periods begin at the start of the forecat period and extend through 
the entire 5-day forecast period from 0-120 hours.
